{
  "texts": [
    "Mind-Spore Graph Learning (Huawei; Wu et al. 2021b) is an efficient graph learning framework based on MindSpore (Huawei).",
    "It uses MindSpore's graph-computing fusion capabilities and automatic operator compilation technology to achieve efficient graph model training and reasoning, greatly accelerating the research and development process of graph learning models.",
    "DIG (Liu et al. 2021b) is a comprehensive and easy-to-use research library for deep learning of graphs, which provides a unified testing platform for researchers.",
    "DIG not only supports high-level graph research tasks such as graph generation and self-supervised learning but also has strong interpretability and the ability to handle complex graph structures such as 3D graphs.",
    "It enables researchers to focus more on algorithm innovation and optimization without worrying about the underlying implementation details."
  ]
}